-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
README
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a small "breathing LED" demo program for the Atmel ATTiny13
microcontroller.

Requirements
------------

 * Software:
   * gcc-avr
   * avr-libc
   * avrdude (or any other AVR programming software)

 * Hardware:
   * Atmel ATtiny13 microcontroller
   * A breadboard (optional, you could also solder all the stuff, of course)
   * Some wires for the breadboard
   * A LED
   * A small (e.g. 4K7) resistor for the LED (optional, but recommended)
   * AVR programmer device (e.g. USBprog with the avrispmk2 firmware) that
     can power the ATtiny13 (or a 3V battery instead).

Building
--------

 $ make

Flashing
--------

 $ make flash

Datasheets
----------

 * ATtiny13:
   * Summary: http://atmel.com/dyn/resources/prod_documents/2535S.pdf
   * Datasheet: http://atmel.com/dyn/resources/prod_documents/doc2535.pdf

 * ATtiny13A:
   * Summary: http://atmel.com/dyn/resources/prod_documents/8126S.pdf
   * Datasheet: http://atmel.com/dyn/resources/prod_documents/doc8126.pdf

 * USBProg:
   * Website: http://www.embedded-projects.net/index.php?page_id=135
   * AVRISP mkII code: http://www.embedded-projects.net/index.php?page_id=148

